            <item>
                <title>Medium</title>
                <description>&lt;p&gt;For a long time, I was thinking about a tool that will provide a set of CSS custom properties with the mouse position, scroll position, random values etc. And since I didn’t find anything that I would like, I decided to write the tool myself. I called it “Medium” because it connects CSS and JS worlds. The library itself is quite simple, but I used it for a few demos on CodePen and it really speeds things up. Now it’s &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/sfi0zy/medium&quot;&gt;available on GitHub&lt;/a&gt; and as &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npmjs.com/package/css.medium.js&quot;&gt;NPM package&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <pubDate>Sun, 19 Feb 2023 00:00:00 +0300</pubDate>
